S(x) = \sum\limits_{k=1}^{\infty}\dfrac{x^2}{1+(kx)^2}
\lim\limits_{k\rightarrow \infty} S(1/k) = 0
S(0) = 0
x
S(x)
S_n(x)
 S_n(x)=\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{x^2}{1+k^2x^2}\\ 
 \begin{align} S(x)-S_n(x) &=\sum_{k={n+1}}^\infty\frac{x^2}{1+k^2x^2}\\ &=\sum_{k={n+1}}^\infty\frac1{1/x^2+k^2}\\ &\le\sum_{k={n+1}}^\infty\frac1{k^2}\\ &\le\frac1n \end{align} 
